<mxfile host="app.diagrams.net">
  <diagram name="Page-1" id="CElwATwhmrqS2UhVftOB">
    <mxGraphModel dx="2691" dy="700" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="dD3OxyqSIHmNCJqEZoo5-2" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;labelPosition=center;verticalLabelPosition=middle;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;This handover describes a &lt;b&gt;production-ready Tenant Resolution Module&lt;/b&gt; for a &lt;b&gt;multi-tenant SaaS CRM&lt;/b&gt; build with &lt;b&gt;ASP.NET Core (.NET 8)&lt;/b&gt; using &lt;b&gt;Clean Architecture, DDD-lite&lt;/b&gt;, and a &lt;b&gt;Modular Monolith&lt;/b&gt;. The emphasis is on preserving isolation, keeping architecture clean, and avoiding unnecessary redesigns.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;High-level purpose&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;The system must determine which tenant (customer/company) an incoming HTTP request belongs to before any business logic or database access occurs.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;For example:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Incoming Request&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Determine Tenant&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Store Tenant in Request Context&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Business Logic&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Database only returns that tenant&#39;s data&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;The application code should never manually pass &lt;b&gt;tenantId &lt;/b&gt;everywhere. Instead, it automatically reads the current tenant from a shared request-scoped context.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="800" width="720" x="-480" y="80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
